title: SFH to attend senior health officials meetings in Hangzhou and Beijing
content_text:
p>
    The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr York Chow, will depart for Hangzhou 
    this afternoon (November 1) to attend the cross-straits exchange session on 
    health-care reform and development, which will be held on November 2 and 3. The exchange session is organised by the China Health Economics Association. 
    Dr Chow will brief the meeting on the latest developments of health-care 
    reform in Hong Kong. He will also take the opportunity to exchange views on 
    health protection systems and hospital management with health officials from

health protection systems and hospital management with health officials from 
    the Mainland, Taiwan, Hong Kong and Macao to foster co-operation among the 
    four places. Dr Chow will then leave for Beijing on Thursday afternoon (November 3) for 
    the 10th Joint Meeting of Senior Health Officials of the Mainland, Hong Kong 
    and Macao on November 4. During the meeting, senior health officials will exchange views and share 
    experiences in four areas - hospital accreditation, prevention and control

experiences in four areas - hospital accreditation, prevention and control 
    of non-communicable diseases, tobacco control, and the system of general 
    practitioners and specialists - to deepen co-operation between the three 
    places. It is hoped that the three places can complement each other's 
    strengths with a common objective of safeguarding the health of their 
    communities.  Dr Chow will deliver a speech at the opening ceremony of the Joint Meeting 
    outlining Hong Kong's work progress and future plans in the above areas. Members of the Hong Kong delegation attending the Joint Meeting will include

the Director of Health, Dr Lam Ping-yan, and the Hospital Authority's Chief 
    Executive, Dr Leung Pak-yin. Dr Chow will return to Hong Kong on Saturday afternoon (November 5).
